title: Marquee games offer SEC East teams to flex muscles vs. West
text: > Texas Marquee games offer SEC East teams to flex muscles vs. West FILE - In this Sept. 26, 2015, file photo, Alabama quarterback Jake Coker (14) throws a pass during the first half of an NCAA college football game against Louisiana Monroe in Tuscaloosa, Ala. In Athens, Georgia, the Bulldogs (4-0, 2-0) host No. 13 Alabama (3-1, 0-1), on Saturday, which looks to bounce back from a 43-37 home loss to Ole Miss nearly two weeks ago. It's the first meeting between the schools since the 2012 SEC title game won 32-28 by the Crimson Tide. (AP Photo/Jonathan Bachman, File)
